    <text>
        <body>
            <div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1947-11-12T18:00:00-05:00"
                frus:doc-dateTime-min="1947-11-12T18:00:00-05:00" n="391"
                subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d391">
                <note rend="inline" type="source">832.1561/11–1047: Telegram</note>
                <head>
                    <hi rend="italic">The <gloss type="from">Secretary of State</gloss> to the
                            <gloss type="to">Embassy in Brazil</gloss>
                    </hi>
                </head>
                <opener>
                    <seg rendition="#left">
                        <hi rend="smallcaps">confidential</hi>
                    </seg>
                    <dateline rendition="#right">
                        <placeName>
                            <hi rend="smallcaps">Washington</hi>
                        </placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1947-11-12T18:00:00-05:00"
                            >November 12, 1947—6 p.m.</date>
                    </dateline>
                </opener>
                <p>1269. <gloss target="#t_urtel1">Urtel</gloss> 1566 Nov 10.<note n="6"
                        xml:id="d391fn1">Not printed.</note>
                    <gloss target="#t_Braz1">Braz</gloss>
                    <gloss target="#t_Emb1">Emb</gloss> has informed Dept receipt <gloss
                        target="#t_FonOff1">FonOff</gloss> cable making following points: <list>
                        <label>
                            <hi rend="italic">a</hi>)</label>
                        <item>priority dock space granted only Lloyd Brasileiro not other <gloss
                                target="#t_Braz1">Braz</gloss>
                            <gloss target="#t_Cos1">cos</gloss>
                        </item>
                        <label>
                            <hi rend="italic">b</hi>)</label>
                        <item>purpose priority to assure supply foodstuffs from other <gloss
                                target="#t_Braz1">Braz</gloss> ports</item>
                        <label>
                            <hi rend="italic">c</hi>)</label>
                        <item>preferences now ineffective since port Rio now uncongested</item>
                        <label>
                            <hi rend="italic">d</hi>)</label>
                        <item>at present not single vessel awaiting berth.</item>
                    </list>
                </p>
                <p>Your comments desired. Points <hi rend="italic">a</hi> and <hi rend="italic"
                        >b</hi> appear specious. Are points <hi rend="italic">c</hi> and <hi
                        rend="italic">d</hi> accurate? Even if so discrimination could be restored
                    at any <pb facs="0456" n="440" xml:id="pg_440"/> time. You will recall that
                        <gloss target="#t_Pres1">Pres</gloss> Dutra informed <gloss target="#t_Amb1"
                        >Amb</gloss> Pawley he would immediately issue instructions cease
                    discrimination between vessels flying <gloss target="#t_Braz1">Braz</gloss> and
                    Am flags (pgh 1 <gloss target="#t_urtel1">urtel</gloss> 1324 Sept 20<note n="7"
                        xml:id="d391fn2">Not printed.</note>). <gloss target="#t_FonOff1"
                        >FonOff</gloss> explanation in no way appears to implement this
                    assurance.</p>
                <closer>
                    <signed>
                        <hi rend="smallcaps">Marshall</hi>
                    </signed>
                </closer>
            </div>
        </body>
